ZH: 这个罪犯终于要伏法了。
EN: The criminal is finally going to face justice.
ZH: 他逃避了很久，终于也要伏法了。
EN: He has been on the run for a long time, but now he must face the consequences.
ZH: 伏法是社会的一种正义。
EN: Facing justice is a form of justice in society.
ZH: 这个案件已经审理了很长时间，终于该伏法了。
EN: This case has been under investigation for a long time, and it is finally time for justice to be served.
ZH: 只有伏法，才能让所有人都感到公平。
EN: Only by facing justice can everyone feel a sense of fairness.
ZH: 那些违法的人必须要伏法。
EN: Those who break the law must face justice.
ZH: 对于犯罪行为，伏法是唯一的选择。
EN: Facing justice is the only option for criminal behavior.
ZH: 他犯下这个错误必须得伏法。
EN: He must face the consequences for his mistake.
ZH: 在这个社会中，每个人都必须要伏法。
EN: In this society, everyone must face justice.
ZH: 他们的罪恶最终也要伏法。
EN: Their sins will eventually catch up with them.
ZH: 这是一个公正的社会，违法的人都会伏法。
EN: This is a just society, and those who break the law will face justice.
ZH: 只有伏法，才能让社会更加和谐。
EN: Only by facing justice can society become more harmonious.
ZH: 他终于要面对所犯的错误，伏法了。
EN: He is finally going to face the consequences of his actions.
ZH: 对于他们的犯罪行为，他们只能伏法。
EN: They can only face justice for their criminal behavior.
ZH: 谁犯了错都要伏法。
EN: Whoever makes a mistake must face the consequences.
ZH: 无论多么隐蔽，违法行为都会终究伏法。
EN: No matter how hidden, illegal actions will eventually face justice.
ZH: 自己犯的错，终究还是要伏法。
EN: One must face the consequences of their own mistakes.
ZH: 不管是否公开或者私下，都有不少人最终会伏法。
EN: Whether in public or in private, many people will eventually face justice.
ZH: 所有的恶行都会伏法，不能逃脱处罚。
EN: All evil deeds will face justice and cannot escape punishment.
